servers: items[1]{url,description}:
    https://coda.io/apis/v1,Coda API (v1)
tags: items[16]{name,description}:
    Account,At this time, the API exposes some limited information about your account. However, `/whoami` is a good endpoint to hit to verify that you're hitting the API correctly and that your token is working as expected.

    Analytics,This API offers analytics data for your docs and Packs over time.
    Automations,This API allows you to trigger automations.
    Columns,While columns in Coda have user-friendly names, they also have immutable IDs that are used when reading and writing rows. These endpoints let you query the columns in a table and get basic information about them.

    Controls,Controls provide a user-friendly way to input a value that can affect other parts of the doc. This API lets you list controls and get their current values.

    Docs,Coda docs are foundational, top-level collaborative projects that contain pages. The API lets you list and search your docs to obtain basic metadata like titles and ownership information.

    Folders,Folders help you organize your docs within workspaces. This API lets you list, create, update, and delete folders.

    Formulas,Formulas can be great for performing one-off computations, or used with tables and other formulas to compute a single value. With this API, you can discover formulas in a doc and obtain computed results.

    Miscellaneous,These endpoints wouldn't fit anywhere else, but you may find them useful when working with Coda.

    Packs,This API allows you to manage Packs that you have developed as well as list publicly available Coda packs.

    Pages,Pages in Coda offer canvases containing rich text, tables, controls, and other objects. At this time, this API lets you list and access pages in a doc.

    Permissions,This API lets you manage sharing and permissions for your docs.
    Publishing,Coda docs can be published publicly and associated with categories to help the world discover them. This API lets you manage the publishing settings of your docs.

    Rows,You'll likely use this part of the API the most. These endpoints let you retrieve row data from tables in Coda as well as create, upsert, update, and delete them. Most of these endpoints work for both base tables and views, but for inserting/upsering rows, you must use a base table.

    Tables and Views,If you're here, you know the power of tables in Coda. This API lets you list the tables and views in a Coda doc and obtain basic schema information.

    Workspaces,This API allows you to manage your workspace's membership and get analytics on membership over time.

